Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email EastEnders viewers couldn't stop laughing on Thursday as Dot Branning stumbled on internet porn.
The God-fearing favourite on Albert Square was trying to innocent use Google to look up 'bushes', and she was left totally stunned by what she found.
The X-rated results weren't shown to viewers during the hilarious scene, but poor Dot looked horrified as she made a quick move to shut the laptop and take a break.
Dot Eastenders Abbi later asked how she was getting on, and she complained about "ladies popping up with no bras".
Viewers loved the lighthearted moment, and one even described it as the "best ever" EastEnders opening.
Dot Eastenders (Photo: BBC) Dot Eastenders (Photo: BBC) Another fan tweeted: "Dots face when getting the results after typing 'bushes' into a search engine"
A different teased: "Oh Dot, you dirty mare"
It was a much different story by the end of the episode , with Dot - whose eyesight has been worrying her more recently - finding herself in a car crash. 
She was using Jack's sat nav to help her drive grandson Matthew to the local garden centre.
Video Loading Video Unavailable Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Watch this video again Video will play in  Dot Cotton in car crash horror on Eastenders Share this video Watch Next However, the electronic voice began giving faulty instructions, and Dot was seen panicking as her confidence behind the wheel disappeared - but it wasn't over.
In the closing moments, viewers saw her miss a 'no entry sign' and head towards oncoming traffic, and while she swerved off the round and into a verge her health was unknown as the credits rolled.
